stories: My reflection is that there's an imbalance in community resources, before suburbanites jump to conclusions, let me make my point. Currently, only small businesses pay local taxes. No individual contributes to the community fund. I've noticed town-funded playgrounds, streetlights, abandoned community centers, and councilors' pet projects like community centers, all of which are not essential within town limits. I was astonished by how much our town provides municipal services in the larger towns, thus swelling the town budget. I saw on TV last night how a local program was teaching kids how to build a birdhouse, couldn't the parents do that? Yes, I pay property taxes. But I'm certain once our town folk get the full bill without the town funds, we'll be more frugal, and on the community center...rent what space you need and help the rental market. In my previous job, I'd ask my colleagues, "how do you prioritize your expenses?"
